cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with wireless networks and their information-theoretic properties, which are typically studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses cooperative communication protocols, which are commonly used in wireless networks (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper presents results for multi-source multi-sink networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The evaluation of degrees of freedom in single-source multi-sink networks involves the use of linear algebra and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the field of machine learning and optimization (cs.MM) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
